Similar to JRA-2644, but from a different angle. Instead of focusing on extending what users get regarding project notifications - allowing them to turn things off.

EG: No matter what, I dont want to recieve emails about comments on any project ... or I dont want to recieve notifications at all as I am going on holiday and will catch up later.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2641].
  {panel}

Say I search JIRA n times a day.  For (n-1) searches, I will have a saved search in my session.  This means I end up on the 'View' filter tab, which doesn't have any search fields.

This is all fine, *if* my last search is relevant to me.  However, on average, it isn't.  This means I have to click on the 'Edit' tab to get anything useful.

Couldn't the extra info and links on the 'View' page be squeezed onto the top of the 'Edit' page?

